info.title: Writesonic Docs
info.description:
This is the documentation for Writesonic's API. To be able to test the API, please register an account and request an api key at [Writesonic](https://writesonic.com).
Please check out the tutorials section for more information
  • [Find your API key](../docs/Find%20Api%20Key)
  • [Test an endpoint](../docs/Test%20An%20Endpoint)

Writesonic API has been upgraded to V2(beta) version. [Click here to read V2 docs (beta)](../api-docs/v2.html)
Note - as all APIs are backwards-compatible, old endpoints will not be impacted by this change.

For any queries write us to at support@writesonic.com

post.description: 4-step, simplified GPT-3 article writer that can write unique articles instantly.

example.article_title: Supporting life on Mars is difficult but possible
example.article_intro: Life on Mars may seem like a distant dreamâ€”at least until it's actually possible. The Red Planet has just started to warm up, but increasing land and water temperatures there could keep humans alive for many years. Or at least that's what the latest estimates say. Even with NASA still planning a return to the Moon by 2020, Mars is a far cry from being autonomous self-sustaining society. But what if we could help our Mars friends already on Earth? Could we establish human settlements there as a way to boost local populations and bring us more than just another planet in a system? In this blog post, we take a look at how creating settlements on Mars would be possible. While it might seem like science fiction, the idea of creating colonies on another world doesn't seem so far-fetched these days. And research is only getting started on how such recreations of our past can help mankind conquer fear and depression while also turning back time to save the world...

post.description: A chatbot like ChatGPT but with real-time data, images & voice search. Chatsonic - AI-powered assistant enables text and image creation. It is a ChatGPT-like conversational AI chatbot but with real-time data, images & voice search. It is built on a powerful connection with Google search that helps to come up with hyper-relevant, factual & latest content to generate unique copy and digital artwork using AI. ### Features of this API - enable/disable real-time Google search - enable/disable memory functionality - talk to ChatSonic in 24 languages Read this guide to learn how to use the [memory functionality](https://docs.writesonic.com/reference/memory-functionality) in ChatSonic

enable_google_results.title: Enable Google Results
enable_google_results.description: If enabled, ChatSonic will use Google search results to answer the question. This is useful when trained AI model doesn't have an answer to the question.

enable_memory.title: Enable Memory
enable_memory.description: If enabled, ChatSonic will remember the previous conversation and will try to continue the conversation.

example.article_title: Supporting life on Mars is difficult but possible
example.article_intro: Life on Mars may seem like a distant dreamâ€”at least until it's actually possible. The Red Planet has just started to warm up, but increasing land and water temperatures there could keep humans alive for many years. Or at least that's what the latest estimates say. Even with NASA still planning a return to the Moon by 2020, Mars is a far cry from being autonomous self-sustaining society. But what if we could help our Mars friends already on Earth? Could we establish human settlements there as a way to boost local populations and bring us more than just another planet in a system? In this blog post, we take a look at how creating settlements on Mars would be possible. While it might seem like science fiction, the idea of creating colonies on another world doesn't seem so far-fetched these days. And research is only getting started on how such recreations of our past can help mankind conquer fear and depression while also turning back time to save the world...
